<span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">Letterpress printing is one the oldest forms of printing known to man. It involves laborious work on seemingly ancient machinery and a whole lot of patience on the printer‚Äôs part. So why do we do it in such a digital age? Because it‚Äôs awesome.</span>
<h4><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">Letterpress Printing is an Artform</span></h4>
<span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">The lines are sharp, the colors are vibrant and it‚Äôs the only form of printing that leaves an actual impression in the paper, making you want to touch it and run your fingers over the markings. Are there faster and easier forms of printing out there? Sure are. Does that mean they‚Äôre better? Not necessarily.¬† Letterpress printing brings character to a simple piece of paper, which is something that you just won‚Äôt get with more modern printing styles.</span>

